From 20th March 2021, further restrictions on freedom of movement will be introduced on the Estonian Western Islands Saaremaa and Muhu. People are only allowed to leave their place of residence for the following reasons:

1) get the everyday essentials (including food, medicine) from places listed in clause 3 of this Order near their place of residence or place of stay because it is otherwise impossible;
2) go see a health care professional for medical reasons;
3) take a pet for a walk or to a veterinarian;
4) take their child to nursery school and bring their child home;
5) take a walk or exercise outside alone or together with their family;
6) move around on their property, do gardening, do forestry or agricultural work and go fishing;
7) go help the elderly, disabled people and others in need of assistance if personal protective equipment is used;
8) go to work if the person’s employer has not allowed or the nature of work does not enable telecommuting.

Additionally, a requirement to carry identification documents upon departure from home is imposed.

From 30th March 2021, further restrictions on freedom of movement will be introduced on the Estonian Western Islands Saaremaa and Muhu. People are only allowed to leave their place of residence for the following reasons:

1) get the everyday essentials (including food, medicine) from places listed in clause 3 of this Order near their place of residence or place of stay because it is otherwise impossible;
2) go see a health care professional for medical reasons;
3) take a pet for a walk or to a veterinarian;
4) take their child to nursery school and bring their child home;
5) take a walk or exercise outside alone or together with their family;
6) move around on their property, do gardening, do forestry or agricultural work and go fishing;
7) go help the elderly, disabled people and others in need of assistance if personal protective equipment is used;
8) go to work if the person’s employer has not allowed or the nature of work does not enable telecommuting.

Additionally, a requirement to carry identification documents upon departure from home is imposed. UPDATE: The lockdown and restrictions on movement imposed on the residents of Saaremaa and Muhu municipalities is being lifted on the 27th April 2020.

